Every diagram has a purpose.

Every diagram answers a specific question.

Together they tell the complete architectural story.

Final Thoughts

Architecture isn’t about choosing the “best” notation.

It’s about communicating decisions effectively.

* EDGY helps us understand the enterprise.
* C4 helps us understand software.
* Mermaid helps us communicate both.

Used together, they provide a consistent journey from strategy to implementation while keeping architecture understandable for everyone—from executives to developers.

Rather than debating which approach is superior, consider how each contributes to a more complete architectural narrative.

The best architecture repositories don’t standardize on a single diagram.

They standardize on answering the right questions.

